/* 1123_daemon_dream.iii -- THE AUTOCATALYTIC LOOP, END TO END, KERNEL-GOVERNED.
 *
 * The headline: a seeded dream hallucinates candidate optimizations, the synthesizer attempts CIC
 * proofs, and the kernel sieve disposes -- autonomously discovering + sealing mathematically-true
 * optimizations the cost-minimizing extractor would never propose, while discarding every false dream.
 *
 * Drives forcefield/daemon_dream::daemon_dream_kat: 99 =
 *   (1) the dream's kernel-certified count == an INDEPENDENT count of the true candidates in the seeded
 *       stream (the kernel sealed EXACTLY the mathematically-true identities -- none false, none missed);
 *   (2) NON-VACUOUS: the dream discovered >= 1 real optimization;
 *   (3) every sealed entry is a true identity (the kernel leash holds though the mutagen lies 3/4 of the time);
 *   (4) DETERMINISM (M2): the same seed yields the same discovery count -- the dream is replayable/auditable;
 *   (5) budget=0: the synthesizer times out every cycle -> ZERO discoveries.
 *
 * The egraph PROPOSES (stochastically, but seeded); the CIC kernel DISPOSES.  The "Golden Shift" --
 * promoting a discovery into the compiler + reseal -- is the OPERATOR-gated step, never autonomous. */
module corpus_1123

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn daemon_dream_kat() -> u64 from "daemon_dream.iii"

fn main() -> u64 {
    let r : u64 = daemon_dream_kat()
    if r != 99u64 { return r }
    return 99u64
}
